<h1>Problem 1741 - 2009 China TST Test 5 P3 of 3</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let nonnegative real numbers \(a_{1},a_{2},a_{3},a_{4}\) satisfy \(a_{1} + a_{2} + a_{3} + a_{4} = 1.\) Prove that
\begin{align*}
 \max\left\{\sum_{i=1}^4{\sqrt {a_{i}^2 + a_{i}a_{i - 1} + a_{i - 1}^2 + a_{i - 1}a_{i - 2}}}, \sum_{i=1}^4{\sqrt {a_{i}^2 + a_{i}a_{i + 1} + a_{i + 1}^2 + a_{i + 1}a_{i + 2}}}\right\}&amp;\ge 2.\end{align*}
where for all integers \(i, a_{i + 4} = a_{i}\) holds.</p>
